gland<ref>[http://www.cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Records/Netherlands/Icct/Highest_Team_Totals_Netherlands.html Netherlands totals of 200 and more in an innings in the ICC Trophy] at Cricket Archive</ref>\n*Highest individual innings: 169 not out, [[Rupert Gomes]] v. [[Israeli cricket team|Israel]], 4 June 1990 at [[Amstelveen]], Netherlands<ref>[http://www.cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Records/Netherlands/Icct/Highest_Player_Scores_Netherlands.html Individual scores of 100 and more in an innings for Netherlands in the ICC Trophy] at Cricket Archive</ref>\n*Best innings bowling: 7/9, [[Asim Khan (cricketer)|Asim Khan]] v. [[East and Central African cricket team|East & Central Africa]], 24 March 1997 at [[Royal Military College, Kuala Lumpur]], Malaysia<ref>[http://www.cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Records/Netherlands/Icct/Best_Innings_Bowling_Netherlands.html Five or more wickets in an innings for Netherlands in the ICC Trophy] at Cricket Archive</ref>\n\n==Notable players==\n{{Update|section|date=February 2019}}\n[[Image:Ryan ten doeschate.jpg|right|thumbnail|right|[[Ryan ten Doeschate]] currently holds the record for the highest batting average in ODI cricket.]]\n\nSeveral Dutch cricketers have also played at first-class level elsewhere, the most successful of these probably being [[Roland Lefebvre]] who played for [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]] and [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]] in English [[county cricket]] as well as for [[Canterbury cricket team|Canterbury]] in New Zealand.\n\nDutch players to have played first class cricket outside of the Intercontinental Cup include:\n\n*[[Ryan ten Doeschate]] \u2013 Playing for [[Essex Eagles|Essex]], [[Canterbury Wizards]], [[Kolkata Knight Riders]] and the [[Mashonaland Eagles]]\n*[[Dirk Nannes]] \u2013 who has played for the [[Victorian Bushrangers]] in Australia, the [[Delhi Daredevils]], the [[Royal Challengers Bangalore]] and the [[Chennai Super Kings]] in the IPL, and has played [[List of Australia Twenty20 International cricketers|T20I]] and [[List of Australia ODI cricketers|ODI]] cricket for Australia.\n*[[Nolan Clarke]] \u2013 who played for [[Barbados]] from 1969/70 until 1976/77.\n*[[Tom Cooper (cricketer)|Tom Cooper]] \u2013 who currently plays first class cricket for [[South Australia cricket team|South Australia]]\n*[[Michael Swart]] - who played for [[Western Australia cricket team | Western Australia]] from 2010 until 2011.\n*[[Paul-Jan Bakker]] \u2013 who played for [[Hampshire County Cricket Club|Hampshire]] from 1986 until 1992.\n*[[Alexei Kervezee]] \u2013 Playing for [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]] since 2007.\n*[[Bill Glerum]] \u2013 who played one first class game for the Free Foresters in 1957.\n*[[Carst Posthuma]] \u2013 who played five first class games for [[London County Cricket Club]] in 1903.\n*[[Darron Reekers]] \u2013 who played three first-class games for [[Otago]] in 1997/98 and List A matches for both Otago and Canterbury (1994/95-2001/02).\n*[[Daan van Bunge]] \u2013 who played for [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]] in 2004.\n*[[Andre van Troost]] \u2013 who played for [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]] from 1991 to 1998, and for [[Griqualand West]] in the 1994/95 season in South Africa.\n*[[Bastiaan Zuiderent|Bas Zuiderent]] \u2013 who played for [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]] from 2001 to 2003.\n*[[Timm van der Gugten]] \u2013 Played for [[New South Wales cricket team|New South Wales]] and others in Australia and New Zealand. Now playing for [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]].\n*[[Logan van Beek]] - who currently plays for [[Wellington Firebirds]] and previously represented [[Canterbury Wizards]]\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/527835.html|title=14th Match: New South Wales v Western Australia at Sydney, Nov 25\u201328, 2011 \u2013 Cricket Scorecard \u2013 ESPN Cricinfo|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\n\n===Playing staff===\nThis list