rs7      = 2010\u20132011 | clubs7  = [[Al-Fateh SC|Al-Fateh]]                    | caps7  = 21 | goals7  = 0\n| years8      = 2011      | clubs8  = \u2192 [[Dubai CSC|Dubai]] (loan)                | caps8  = 5  | goals8  = 0\n| years9      = 2011\u20132012 | clubs9  = [[Al-Nasr SC (Kuwait)|Al-Nasr]]             | caps9  = 19 | goals9  = 3\n| years10     = 2012\u20132013 | clubs10 = [[Ettifaq FC|Al-Ettifaq]]                   | caps10 = 29 | goals10 = 2\n| years11     = 2013\u20132014 | clubs11 = [[Fanja SC|Fanja]]                          | caps11 = 28 | goals11 = 1\n| years12     = 2014\u20132015 | clubs12 = [[Al-Oruba SC|Al-Oruba]]                    | caps12 = 10 | goals12 = 1\n| years13     = 2015\u20132016 | clubs13 = [[Muaither SC|Muaither]]                    | caps13 = ?  | goals13 = ?\n| years14     = 2016\u20132017 | clubs14 = [[Al-Markhiya SC|Al-Markhiya]]              | caps14 = ?  | goals14 = ?\n| years15     = 2017\u20132019 | clubs15 = [[Al-Mesaimeer Sports Club|Mesaimeer]]      | caps15 = ?  | goals15 = ?\n| years16     = 2019\u2013     | clubs16 = [[Al-Markhiya SC|Al-Markhiya]]              | caps16 = ?  | goals16 = ?\n| nationalyears1 = 2003\u2013  | nationalteam1 = [[Oman national football team|Oman]]  | nationalcaps1 = 175| nationalgoals1 = 23\n| pcupdate = 14 July 2019\n| ntupdate = 19 November 2019\n}}\n\n'''Ahmed Mubarak Obaid al-Mahaijri''' ({{lang-ar|\u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0645\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0639\u0628\u064a\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u064a\u062c\u0631\u064a}}; born 23 February 1985), commonly known as '''Ahmed Mubarak''' or '''Ahmed Kano''', is an [[Oman]]i [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Al-Markhiya SC|Al-Markhiya]] in the [[Qatari Second Division]].<ref>{{NFT player|id=4984|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nAhmed Mubarak has previously played for various clubs in GCC countries with clubs like [[Al-Wehda Club (Mecca)|Al-Wehda Club]], [[Al-Ahli (Jeddah)|Al-Ahli SC]], [[Al Fateh (Sports Club)|Al-Fateh SC]] and [[Ettifaq FC]] of [[Saudi Arabia|KSA]], [[Al Ain S.C.C.]] and [[Dubai C.S.C.]] of the [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]], [[Al-Wakra]], [[Al Rayyan Sports Club]] and [[Al-Sailiya Sport Club]] of [[Qatar]] and [[Al Naser Sporting Club]] of [[Kuwait]]. On 5 September 2013, he signed a one-year contract with [[2012\u201313 Oman Elite League]] runners-up [[Fanja SC]].<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.kooora.com/?n=268271&pg=8&o=n1005845 | title= \u0641\u0646\u062c\u0627\u0621 \u064a\u062a\u0639\u0627\u0642\u062f \u0645\u0639 \u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0645\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0643\u0627\u0646\u0648 \u0646\u062c\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0646\u062a\u062e\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0645\u0627\u0646\u064a | publisher= Koora.com}}</ref> On 13 July 2014, he signed a one-year contract with his first professional club [[Al-Oruba SC]].<ref>{{cite web | url= http://lo3btna.com/?p=22429 | title= \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0648\u0628\u0629 \u064a\u062a\u0639\u0627\u0642\u062f \u0645\u0639 \u0643\u0627\u0646\u0648 \u0648\u0633\u0639\u062f \u0633\u0647\u064a\u0644 \u0648\u0647\u0627\u0634\u0645 \u0635\u0627\u0644\u062d \u0627\u0644\u064a \u0646\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0635\u0644\u0627\u0644\u0629 | publisher= Lo3btna.com}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAhmed Mubarak is part of the first team squad of the Oman national football team. He was selected for the national team for the first time in 2003, along with [[Ahmed Hadid Al-Mukhaini|Ahmed Hadid]], [[Badar Al-Maimani]] and [[Ali Al Habsi|Ali Al-Habsi]].\n\n===Arabian Gulf Cup===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:KanoGulfCup.png|thumb|right|250px|Ahmed Mubarak celebrating his goal against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] at [[2014 Gulf Cup of Nations]]]] -->\nAhmed Mubarak has made appearances in the [[2003 Gulf Cup of Nations|2003]], [[2004 Gulf Cup of Nations|2004]], [[2007 Gulf Cup of Nations|2007]], [[2009 Gulf Cup of Nations|2009]], [[2010 Gulf Cup of Nations|2010]], [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|2013]], [[2014 Gulf Cup of Nations|2014]], and the [[2017 Gulf Cup of Nations|2017]] editions of the Arabian Gulf Cup.\nIn the 2003 edition of the tournament, he scored one goal in an important 2\u22120 win against the [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]]. In the 2014 edition, he scored one goal in a close 1\u22121 draw against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]. And in the 2017 edition, he managed to score a critical [[penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]] in a difficult 1\u22120 win against the hosts [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]].<ref>{{cite web | url= https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/12/25/asia/gulf-cup/kuwait/oman/2701692/?ICID=PL_MS_06 | title= Kuwait vs Oman 0-1 | publisher= soccerway.com | date= 25 December 2017 | accessdate= 10 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nAhmed Mubarak won the most valuable player award of the [[23rd Arabian Gulf Cup|2017 Gulf Cup]] for his role in the success of the Omani team tournament campaign.\n\n===AFC Asian Cup===\nAhmed Mubarak has made appearances in the [[2004 AFC Asian Cup qualification|2004 Asian Cup qualifiers]], the [[2004 AFC Asian Cup|2004 Asian Cup]], the [[2007 AFC Asian Cup qualification|2007 Asian Cup qualifiers]], the [[2007 AFC Asian Cup|2007 Asian Cup]], the [[2011 AFC Asian Cup qualification|2011 Asian Cup qualifiers]], the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup qualification|2015 Asian Cup qualifiers]], the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup|2015 Asian Cup]], and the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup qualification|2019 Asian Cup qualifiers]].\n\n===FIFA World Cup qualification===\nAhmed Mubarak has made a total of four appearances in the [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2006 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], six in the [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2010 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] and fourteen in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]].\nIn the [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2010 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], he scored one goal in a 1\u22121 draw against [[Japan national football team|Japan]].<ref>{{cite web | url= https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2008/06/07/asia/wc-qualifying-asia/oman/japan/537218/ | title= Oman vs Japan 1-1 | publisher= soccerway.com| date=7 June 2008}}</ref>\nHe scored three goals in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]]. The first one came in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Second Round|second round of the FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] in a 2\u22120 win over [[Myanmar national football team|Myanmar]],<ref>{{cite web | url= https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/07/28/asia/wc-qualifying-asia/myanmar/oman/1100674/?ICID=PL_MS_16 | title= Myanmar vs Oman 0-2 | publisher= soccerway.com | date=28 July 2011}}</ref> and the other two goals were scored in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Fourth Round|fourth round of the FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], one in a 2\u22121 win over [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]]<ref>{{cite web | url= https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/asia/matches/round=257777/match=300191850/index.html | title= Oman vs Jordan 2-1 Match Report | publisher= fifa.com}}</ref> and another in a 1\u22122 loss against [[Japan national football team|Japan]].<ref>{{cite web | url= https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/asia/matches/round=257777/match=300191856/index.html | title= Oman vs Japan 1-2 Match Report | publisher= fifa.com}}</ref> Oman entered the last game of group play with a chance to qualify for at least the playoff-round, but a 1\u22120 loss to Jordan eliminated them from the competition.<ref>{{cite web | url= https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/asia/matches/round=257777/match=300191847/index.html | title= Jordan vs Oman 1-0 Match Report | publisher= fifa.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Division\n!colsp